# AI3 Project Agent Rules

## Formatting Guidelines

### No Emoji or Em-dash
- Do not use emoji characters in any files
- Do not use em-dash (â€”) characters; use regular hyphens or spaces instead
- Keep all text clean and plain

### Code Style
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Keep comments concise and focused
- Follow ES6+ standards for JavaScript
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)

### Documentation
- Write clear, direct documentation without decorative elements
- Use markdown formatting for structure (headings, lists, tables)
- Include code examples where helpful
- Maintain a professional tone

## Project Structure
- Root: Configuration and documentation files
- HTML/CSS/JS: Client-side application files
- README.md: Project overview and setup instructions

## Dependencies
- ethers.js: For blockchain interactions
- vite: Build tool and dev server

